Class TypeSymbol

  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArraySymbol, CompositeSymbol, EnumerationSymbol, ErrorType

    public abstract class TypeSymbol
extends Symbol
    Symbol table entries associated with types in a Bramspr-program are all subclasses of this abstract class. These entities are array types (see ArraySymbol), composite types (see CompositeSymbol) and enumerated types (see EnumerationSymbol). They don't share certain information apart from what is already specified in Symbol, this class is nothing more than an empty subclass of that class.

        public abstract java.lang.String getDescriptor()
        Returns the descriptor of this type. Is often the same as the signature, but for JVM Objects the signature starts with L and ends with ;. The descriptor does not.

      • getSignature

        public java.lang.String getSignature()
        Returns the signature of a type. E.g. "Z" (boolean), "[I" (integer array), "Ljava/lang/String;" (string) or "Bramspr$CA" (user defined type)
